position":[318,520],"id":"e3404dd0-8302-fdd8-3b07-e828d1146fb1","name":"Note: Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Rejected Input\n\ngoogleSheets — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,1030],"id":"f956f243-94da-fe82-a92e-202ce21b3dcd","name":"Note: Record Rejected Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Classify with AI\n\nLLM classification into: Question, Complaint, Feedback (+fallback). Output port order matches this list.\n\nPorts: ①→ Store as Question · ②→ Store as Complaint, Capture Failure Context · ③→ Store as Feedback · ④→ Alert Slack — Other\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"ba8b67e8-27bb-80a1-7ef9-447f845d5fdf","name":"Note: Classify with AI"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Google Gemini Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `models/gemini-2.5-flash`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Classify with AI** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 Google AI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,1090],"id":"f325a3b1-8c39-6297-59e3-7499b39af786","name":"Note: Google Gemini Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Question\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,40],"id":"6ee24637-a632-4b74-87b4-6ef91717e6a8","name":"Note: Store as Question"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Complaint\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,490],"id":"321b5c8e-10ee-308a-5449-ba6ef6529b87","name":"Note: Store as Complaint"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Feedback\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1857,940],"id":"0263d0d6-53cd-d740-77e6-c3818a09ab36","name":"Note: Store as Feedback"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Alert Slack — Other\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2181,1390],"id":"03d3f119-d693-d9a6-cc75-3702ddbd9059","name":"Note: Alert Slack — Other"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Reunite Branches\n\nRejoins 4 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2829,520],"id":"8e027db5-468e-d28a-5f09-32bd12705db5","name":"Note: Reunite Branches"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"a5e897a3-2389-6d85-a74a-dc63aa73e99e","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"3d15554c-3e26-b772-d723-688c55369b86","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"b13b2a36-0150-d08e-f170-238adb3fa0f8","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"5799bb3f-e39d-3a6f-60df-c112d90247d2","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per request (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"4d32ec66-6799-2c8a-24d0-4991a24d945b","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"1238460f-246e-bea6-bf33-c93db2e8d5bc","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,520],"id":"d5d0b378-6462-9653-ce09-8b963d83c0f4","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6069,520],"id":"944f995f-f266-5b23-f952-a089a7bae5a9","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6393,520],"id":"251b23b7-b156-ddde-1aa4-f93faea3a465","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6717,520],"id":"ad0c87bd-9c42-a1c3-d338-a6a1c92108e1","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7041,520],"id":"ede2b02e-4918-97f4-680e-ce25f5c8aa57","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7365,520],"id":"8189fcee-56ae-6e56-9a9d-641897de678a","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7689,520],"id":"f5205573-fc3f-d195-c4ff-123c4f76f535","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Notion)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8013,520],"id":"fa2d0182-c912-8345-857b-39120253a862","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Notion)\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8337,520],"id":"33e3d94e-5c35-327f-55fc-91bf3a3a7e0b","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Notion)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8661,520],"id":"5cf145fc-8982-9f44-d036-0fca7cd2d65b","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8013,1540],"id":"75e87cbb-b844-5e34-bc2b-62490e24ecae","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8337,1540],"id":"bd9fce0c-5dbb-ad87-67c7-876295b195a4","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8661,1540],"id":"934b0036-ac98-f3f3-4573-34b6168ec0a1","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Answer user questions on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nAnswer user questions on autopilot. It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual task automation is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Stamp & Shape Request → Payload Valid? → Classify with AI → Store as Question → Reunite Branches → Stamp Completion Time → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating task automation in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google AI API key; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"9b50cc7e-d4e6-3dab-c8b9-f04e0bd77b12","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"f1e382af-2d9d-cb39-5413-d727031e4ad1","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"b8b0ab36-f559-0dd2-75e2-50e44459fbd5","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"dcbfac60-089d-bbc7-de51-48470797c8fd","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your task automation process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-500],"id":"ff2b23cb-9308-16db-ed37-2ba1269b85ba","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"When Chat Message Received":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Request","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Request":{"main":[[{"node":"Payload Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Payload Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Classify with AI","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Rejected Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Google Gemini Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Classify with AI","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Classify with AI":{"main":[[{"node":"Store as Question","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Store as Complaint","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Store as Feedback","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Alert Slack — Other","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Question":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Complaint":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Feedback":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Alert Slack — Other":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":3}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Reunite Branches":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Notion)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Notion)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"67260dd5-197d-4a11-8a63-f5b562604cef","id":"FDX00215"}